	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My thoughts are: what is intractable and collidable?<br />Certainly I can see a back wall that I expect to be solid, and there is a ledge I can see as well.<br />But the main floor looks like it is just design, and I ought to be able to walk everywhere.  But can I?  Or am I supposed to interact with some of those more complex-looking regions somehow?<br />And I stared at image for a minute before I realized there was a staircase there in the ground.<br /><br />Artistically, it looks good.  But for a game, I would want the edges to be better defined.  I don't want to have to guess about where I can walk.<br /><br />Also, you might try shifting the hues a bit.  The highlights or the shadows or both; try shifting the hues.  It usually looks really good, and you can sometimes use that other hue to add extra detail and definition if you put it in the right spot.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


